{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tipping-content-js","path":"/netherlands","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Dutch law requires that all service charges and taxes are included in the prices that hotels, bars and restaurants publish. Tipping is therefore not necessary, but it is always appreciated as a reward for good service and it's increasingly common. Especially in tourist areas and large hotels, increased tipping is not uncommon. Many Dutch customers will leave €1 or €2, also in bars and simple diners, unless service was poor. For good service in a restaurant, feel free to leave what you feel is appropriate. A 5-10% tip on a restaurant bill is considered a generous reward for good service.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/netherlands","title":"Netherlands","author":"Joni","date":"2019-11-20","image":"netherlands.jpg"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5,"src":"/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/90537/netherlands.jpg","srcSet":"/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/b3ebb/netherlands.jpg 270w,\n/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/95b54/netherlands.jpg 540w,\n/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/90537/netherlands.jpg 1080w,\n/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/3cda3/netherlands.jpg 1620w,\n/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/1f682/netherlands.jpg 2160w,\n/static/fdc6404ed2ddedff717ac19576eeb51d/0b354/netherlands.jpg 6000w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"image":"netherlands.jpg"}}}